    <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Neatly written copy of a book on Ḥanafī jurisprudence and followed by a second work, an abridgment of Wiqāyah al-riwāyah fī masā'il al-hidāyah, on the same topic. A table of contents and an introduction with marginal text precede the main text, with a second, less formally formatted table of contents right before the main text (f. 34). Some collation notations are visible in the far outer margins along with guidewords for the topics, many of which have been partially trimmed.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Title from introductions to text (f. unnumbered 3v, 36r)</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="505" ind1="0" ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">1. f. unnumbered 1v-unnumbered 3r: [Table of contents] -- 2. f. unnumbered 3v-275v: Muʻīn al-muftī ʻalá jawāb al-mustaftī / Muḥammad ibn ʻAbd Allāh -- 4. f. 275v-344r: Mukhtaṣar al-Wiqāyah / ʻUbayd ibn Masʻūd ibn Tāj al-Sharīʻah.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="530" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Also available as a digital facsimile.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="546" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Arabic.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Foliation: Near contemporary foliation in Hindu-Arabic numerals in ink (1-132, 134-172, 172-275), upper left recto; modern foliation in pencil added (286-344), upper left recto.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Layout: 19-21 long lines</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Script: Written in neat naskh in black ink; pointed.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Decoration: Simple headpiece of red half circle divided in thirds by curving lines at the beginning of the table of contents (f. unnumbered 1v), the introduction (f. unnumbered 3v) and the main text (f. 35v); those same page-openings border-ruled in red; rubrications in red.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Binding: Bound in black leather over pasteboard with flap (Type II) with brown onlays of central mandorla, cornerpieces, and two pendants on the vertical axis (no longer present on front cover); flap has matching onlays; spine and fore-edge hinge are reinforced with red leather; blue textile reinforcement on inside flap hinge; endbands in pink and blue chevron pattern.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Origin: The copy was completed in 1131 (1718 or 1719) by Kāẓim ibn ʻAbd Allāh ibn Aḥmad ibn Muḥammad Qāḍīʹzādah al-Ḥasanī al-Ḥusaynī (f. 285v). The introduction is dated Rabīʻ al-thānī 1130 (March 1718) (f. 31r).</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Watermark: Three crescent moons of the same size in a straight line, the points of each one touching the body of the next.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Notes on first leaf recto and inside back cover; partial stamp on first leaf recto.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Brief notes describing the manuscript from Mr. M. S. Khan in Calcutta, India, and dated July 1954, laid in.</subfield>
    </datafield>
